\" layout=\"masonry\" columns=\"3\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]','Gallery','','inherit','closed','closed','','22-revision-v1','','','2018-02-11 19:50:25','2018-02-11 19:50:25','',22,'http://www.richarajput.com/22-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(279,1,'2018-02-12 16:16:29','2018-02-12 16:16:29','&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong>Author: Richa Rajput</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong>Digital Marketing Professional</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong> </strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">“While customers may love your product or service, they’re really going to love the content you produce if it’s helpful to them.” In a crowded business informational place, marketer needs to stand out and this is when Content marketing comes into picture. So, now the question arises what exactly is content marketing.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong>What is Content Marketing ?</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Content marketing is a strategic business process focused on creating and distributing relevant and consistent content to attract and retain clearly defined audience to drive profitable customer action. Good content marketing efforts leads to relationship building and trust among the customers.</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong>Types of Content</strong></span></h6>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Blogs or Guest Posts</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Images</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Infographics</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Videos</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Mailers</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Magazine articles</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Podcasts</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Webinars</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Newsletters</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Powerpoint Presentations</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong>Characteristics of a Good Content</strong></span></h6>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Great content can funnel more traffic to your website and social media pages, strengthen your brand’s reputation and encourage more web visitors to convert into customers. Here are few tips you can adopt to create a quality content: </span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Your content should create emotional appeal and resonance with your customers</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Start with an attractive headline which should be specific and prompting</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Should include a working title and a solid structure</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Tone should be relevant to the users</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Supports your Brand messaging</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Add to conversation than what has already been published</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Should be consistent and authentic</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Content should be clean, concise and short</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Free of errors and poor grammar</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Has a relevant call to action</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Lastly, it should enhance your reader’s experience</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong>Content Marketing Made Simple: A Step by Step Guide</strong></span></h6>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.richarajput.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/blog.jpeg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-281\" src=\"http://www.richarajput.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/blog-300x200.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"353\" height=\"236\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Generation of Content Ideas</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Idea generation isn’t just about waiting for inspiration to strike. You can generate ideas either on your own or in groups. So, now you might be thinking, how you will generate ideas. You can follow these few simple yet effective tips that will help you generate new ideas.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Look for competitor’s content ideas</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Look what people are talking on Quora about your related topic of interest</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use Google auto search to have an idea about the keywords</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Do indulge in technique of Braindump i.e. jotting down the ideas in an organized format that strikes your mind.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use tools like Buzzsumo that tells social media engagements of your generated content.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Content Ideation Process</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">New ideas can be generated with the help of a Content Ideation Process. The steps are as follows:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">New combination of old ideas</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Gathering raw material</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Digesting material</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Unconscious processing</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Eureka Moment</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"2\">\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Build Content Creation Framework</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Content creation is essential to the success of your Inbound Marketing. If you want to be found in the search engines for the phrases that your potential customers search for, then you will have to build an effective content creation framework. An effective framework for content marketing will mean that it has to be repeatable, organized and agile. That’s when you have a proven structure to produce quality content.  You will need to create educational, informative, useful content for your audience based on your detailed understanding of buyer’s personas and the stage that they are at within their buyer’s journey.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>How to build a </strong><strong>Content Creation Framework ?</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Conceptualizing your content</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Planning and setting timelines</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Creating a workflow</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Reviewing your content</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Publishing on different digital platforms and promotion</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Organizing it internally</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Analyzing the results</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"3\">\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Business Story Telling</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">People don’t buy what you do. They buy why you do it. The aim of writing a good content should be to educate and teach your audience, thereby creating an alignment between your business and customers. There are three elements of story telling namely Character, Conflict and Resolution.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Character: </strong>Character consists of First Person: Author i.e. I, Second Person: Audience i.e. You and Third Person: He/ She which may consist of case studies about your customers.</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Conflict: </strong>A good content includes a conflict that fits your prospect’s problems, needs and buyer’s journey stage.</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Resolution: </strong>It includes an effective call to action.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"4\">\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Content Promotions</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Content Promotion is the distribution of content through various media channels like Facebook, Linkedin, Twitter, Instagram, Pinterest, Websites etc. Content Promotions are of two types i.e. <strong>Organic Promotions</strong> which includes SEO, Email Marketing, Social Media Promotions, Influencer, word of mouth, live events and webinars. Second type of Content Promotions are <strong>Paid Promotions </strong>that targets highly specific customers. Examples of Paid Promotions are Search Engine Ads and Social media Ads.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Content Promotion Best Practices:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Include Content optimization to enhance the outcome of your promotion plan</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Include link to landing page and appropriate call to action</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use content promotion calendar to keep a track of the consistency of the content marketing efforts</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use technique of Experimentation and Segmentation to create a list of customers based on their interests.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Analyze results of the published content</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.richarajput.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/content-marketing-benefits.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-285\" src=\"http://www.richarajput.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/content-marketing-benefits-300x194.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"365\" height=\"237\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"5\">\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Repurposing Content</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Are you struggling to come up with new content? Repurposing content is a little-known secret that all smart marketers use to keep driving traffic to their site. There is no doubt that content marketing will enhance your Brand awareness but the problem is, creating content takes a lot of time and effort.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">But what if your best content could go to work for you, again and again, without your having to create anything new? That’s when Repurposing content comes into picture. It is the technique of republishing and recycling your content on different digital media.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">These are big <strong>benefits</strong> that you can’t afford to ignore. If you are <em>not </em>repurposing your content, you are missing out on a huge opportunity for your business.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Allows you to reach more potential customers</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Get more organic search engine traffic</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Improves Search Engine Optimization</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Stop stressing over what to write about</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Supports consistency and create content on ongoing basis</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Devote more time towards making sales</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Now that you know why you should be doing it, let’s look at <strong>Repurposing best Practices</strong>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use internal links and call to action in blogs</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use canonical Tags</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Wait atleast two weeks before republishing content</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Upgrade and update the content that needs to be reposted</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Modify the headline</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Pick only your top performing content and not all the content</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Repost the content on popular website that matches your business</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\" language=\"javascript\">\r\n      var aax_size=\'728x90\';\r\n      var aax_pubname = \'15380c-21\';\r\n      var aax_src=\'302\';\r\n    </script>\r\n    <script type=\"text/javascript\" language=\"javascript\" src=\"http://c.amazon-adsystem.com/aax2/assoc.js\"></script>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"6\">\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Analyzing and Measuring Content Marketing Efforts</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">After producing carefully thought content and distributing it to your audience, the next step is to measure the success of your efforts. Why? Because data is necessary for continual improvement. And if you don’t see results you want, you need to change the status quo. By including a measurement strategy into your content marketing initiative, you can adjust your approach, delivery and determine all possible paths to customer conversion.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Areas of focus in analyzing content:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Brand awareness</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Customer engagement</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Lead Generation</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Customer Conversion and Sales</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Customer Loyalty and retention</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Website Performance</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"7\">\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Developing a Growth Marketing mentality</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Growth Marketing is an integrated approach to grow your business and optimizing your content marketing efforts through constant testing across marketing channels. Various departments which you need to focus for growth marketing are Customer service support, Sales Team, Products and Service Team.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Metrics to focus on:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Traffic on website and social media platforms</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Cost to acquire customers</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Qualified Leads</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Qualified Leads to SQL</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Conversion Rate</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Repeat Customer Rate</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Month over month growth</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Year over year growth</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">If you focus your energy on telling good business story with a carefully strategized content, no matter on which platform or in what context, will win in the long run. Yelling louder won’t help you anymore, only yelling better things will.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>So what’s your story? Are you using content marketing already?</em></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>','Content Marketing: An Art of Communicating without Selling','','publish','open','open','','content-marketing','','','2018-03-07 13:56:58','2018-03-07 13:56:58','',0,'http://www.richarajput.com/?p=279',0,'post','',10),(280,1,'2018-02-12 16:08:00','2018-02-12 16:08:00','','content marketing','','inherit','open','closed','','content-marketing','','','2018-02-12 16:08:00','2018-02-12 16:08:00','',279,'http://www.richarajput.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/content-marketing.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(281,1,'2018-02-12 16:14:37','2018-02-12 16:14:37','','blog','','inherit','open','closed','','blog-2','','','2018-02-12 16:14:37','2018-02-12 16:14:37','',279,'http://www.richarajput.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/blog.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(284,1,'2018-02-12 16:17:28','2018-02-12 16:17:28','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong>Author: Richa Rajput</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong>Digital Marketing Professional</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong> </strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">“While customers may love your product or service, they’re really going to love the content you produce if it’s helpful to them.” In a crowded business informational place, marketer needs to stand out and this is when Content marketing comes into picture. So, now the question arises what exactly is content marketing.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong>What is Content Marketing ?</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Content marketing is a strategic business process focused on creating and distributing relevant and consistent content to attract and retain clearly defined audience to drive profitable customer action. Good content marketing efforts leads to relationship building and trust among the customers.</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong>Types of Content</strong></span></h6>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Blogs or Guest Posts</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Images</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Infographics</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Videos</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Mailers</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Magazine articles</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Podcasts</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Webinars</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Newsletters</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Powerpoint Presentations</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong>Characteristics of a Good Content</strong></span></h6>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Great content can funnel more traffic to your website and social media pages, strengthen your brand’s reputation and encourage more web visitors to convert into customers. Here are few tips you can adopt to create a quality content: </span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Your content should create emotional appeal and resonance with your customers</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Start with an attractive headline which should be specific and prompting</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Should include a working title and a solid structure</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Tone should be relevant to the users</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Supports your Brand messaging</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Add to conversation than what has already been published</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Should be consistent and authentic</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Content should be clean, concise and short</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Free of errors and poor grammar</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Has a relevant call to action</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Lastly, it should enhance your reader’s experience</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong>Content Marketing Made Simple: A Step by Step Guide</strong></span></h6>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.richarajput.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/blog.jpeg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-281\" src=\"http://www.richarajput.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/blog-300x200.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"353\" height=\"236\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Generation of Content Ideas</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Idea generation isn’t just about waiting for inspiration to strike. You can generate ideas either on your own or in groups. So, now you might be thinking, how you will generate ideas. You can follow these few simple yet effective tips that will help you generate new ideas.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Look for competitor’s content ideas</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Look what people are talking on Quora about your related topic of interest</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use Google auto search to have an idea about the keywords</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Do indulge in technique of Braindump i.e. jotting down the ideas in an organized format that strikes your mind.</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use tools like Buzzsumo that tells social media engagements of your generated content.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Content Ideation Process</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">New ideas can be generated with the help of a Content Ideation Process. The steps are as follows:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">New combination of old ideas</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Gathering raw material</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Digesting material</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Unconscious processing</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Eureka Moment</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"2\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Build Content Creation Framework</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Content creation is essential to the success of your Inbound Marketing. If you want to be found in the search engines for the phrases that your potential customers search for, then you will have to build an effective content creation framework. An effective framework for content marketing will mean that it has to be repeatable, organized and agile. That’s when you have a proven structure to produce quality content.  You will need to create educational, informative, useful content for your audience based on your detailed understanding of buyer’s personas and the stage that they are at within their buyer’s journey.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>How to build a </strong><strong>Content Creation Framework ?</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Conceptualizing your content</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Planning and setting timelines</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Creating a workflow</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Reviewing your content</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Publishing on different digital platforms and promotion</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Organizing it internally</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Analyzing the results</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"3\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Business Story Telling</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">People don’t buy what you do. They buy why you do it. The aim of writing a good content should be to educate and teach your audience, thereby creating an alignment between your business and customers. There are three elements of story telling namely Character, Conflict and Resolution.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Character: </strong>Character consists of First Person: Author i.e. I, Second Person: Audience i.e. You and Third Person: He/ She which may consist of case studies about your customers.</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Conflict: </strong>A good content includes a conflict that fits your prospect’s problems, needs and buyer’s journey stage.</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Resolution: </strong>It includes an effective call to action.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"4\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Content Promotions</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Content Promotion is the distribution of content through various media channels like Facebook, Linkedin, Twitter, Instagram, Pinterest, Websites etc. Content Promotions are of two types i.e. <strong>Organic Promotions</strong> which includes SEO, Email Marketing, Social Media Promotions, Influencer, word of mouth, live events and webinars. Second type of Content Promotions are <strong>Paid Promotions </strong>that targets highly specific customers. Examples of Paid Promotions are Search Engine Ads and Social media Ads.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Content Promotion Best Practices:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Include Content optimization to enhance the outcome of your promotion plan</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Include link to landing page and appropriate call to action</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use content promotion calendar to keep a track of the consistency of the content marketing efforts</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use technique of Experimentation and Segmentation to create a list of customers based on their interests.</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Analyze results of the published content</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"5\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Repurposing Content</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Are you struggling to come up with new content? Repurposing content is a little-known secret that all smart marketers use to keep driving traffic to their site. There is no doubt that content marketing will enhance your Brand awareness but the problem is, creating content takes a lot of time and effort.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">But what if your best content could go to work for you, again and again, without your having to create anything new? That’s when Repurposing content comes into picture. It is the technique of republishing and recycling your content on different digital media.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">These are big <strong>benefits</strong> that you can’t afford to ignore. If you are <em>not </em>repurposing your content, you are missing out on a huge opportunity for your business.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Allows you to reach more potential customers</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Get more organic search engine traffic</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Improves Search Engine Optimization</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Stop stressing over what to write about</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Supports consistency and create content on ongoing basis</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Devote more time towards making sales</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Now that you know why you should be doing it, let’s look at <strong>Repurposing best Practices</strong>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use internal links and call to action in blogs</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use canonical Tags</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Wait atleast two weeks before republishing content</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Upgrade and update the content that needs to be reposted</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Modify the headline</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Pick only your top performing content and not all the content</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Repost the content on popular website that matches your business</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"6\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Analyzing and Measuring Content Marketing Efforts</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">After producing carefully thought content and distributing it to your audience, the next step is to measure the success of your efforts. Why? Because data is necessary for continual improvement. And if you don’t see results you want, you need to change the status quo. By including a measurement strategy into your content marketing initiative, you can adjust your approach, delivery and determine all possible paths to customer conversion.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Areas of focus in analyzing content:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Brand awareness</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Customer engagement</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Lead Generation</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Customer Conversion and Sales</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Customer Loyalty and retention</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Website Performance</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"7\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Developing a Growth Marketing mentality</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Growth Marketing is an integrated approach to grow your business and optimizing your content marketing efforts through constant testing across marketing channels. Various departments which you need to focus for growth marketing are Customer service support, Sales Team, Products and Service Team.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Metrics to focus on:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Traffic on website and social media platforms</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Cost to acquire customers</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Qualified Leads</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Qualified Leads to SQL</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Conversion Rate</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Repeat Customer Rate</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Month over month growth</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Year over year growth</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">If you focus your energy on telling good business story with a carefully strategized content, no matter on which platform or in what context, will win in the long run. Yelling louder won’t help you anymore, only yelling better things will.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>So what’s your story? Are you using content marketing already?</em></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>','Content Marketing: An Art of Communicating without Selling','','inherit','closed','closed','','279-revision-v1','','','2018-02-12 16:17:28','2018-02-12 16:17:28','',279,'http://www.richarajput.com/279-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(282,1,'2018-02-12 16:16:29','2018-02-12 16:16:29','<h6 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Content Marketing: An Art of Communicating without Selling</strong></span></h6>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong>Author: Richa Rajput</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong>Digital Marketing Professional</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong> </strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">“While customers may love your product or service, they’re really going to love the content you produce if it’s helpful to them.” In a crowded business informational place, marketer needs to stand out and this is when Content marketing comes into picture. So, now the question arises what exactly is content marketing.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong>What is Content Marketing ?</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Content marketing is a strategic business process focused on creating and distributing relevant and consistent content to attract and retain clearly defined audience to drive profitable customer action. Good content marketing efforts leads to relationship building and trust among the customers.</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong>Types of Content</strong></span></h6>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Blogs or Guest Posts</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Images</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Infographics</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Videos</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Mailers</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Magazine articles</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Podcasts</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Webinars</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Newsletters</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Powerpoint Presentations</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong>Characteristics of a Good Content</strong></span></h6>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Great content can funnel more traffic to your website and social media pages, strengthen your brand’s reputation and encourage more web visitors to convert into customers. Here are few tips you can adopt to create a quality content: </span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Your content should create emotional appeal and resonance with your customers</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Start with an attractive headline which should be specific and prompting</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Should include a working title and a solid structure</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Tone should be relevant to the users</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Supports your Brand messaging</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Add to conversation than what has already been published</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Should be consistent and authentic</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Content should be clean, concise and short</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Free of errors and poor grammar</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Has a relevant call to action</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Lastly, it should enhance your reader’s experience</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong>Content Marketing Made Simple: A Step by Step Guide</strong></span></h6>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.richarajput.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/blog.jpeg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-281\" src=\"http://www.richarajput.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/blog-300x200.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"353\" height=\"236\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Generation of Content Ideas</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Idea generation isn’t just about waiting for inspiration to strike. You can generate ideas either on your own or in groups. So, now you might be thinking, how you will generate ideas. You can follow these few simple yet effective tips that will help you generate new ideas.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Look for competitor’s content ideas</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Look what people are talking on Quora about your related topic of interest</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use Google auto search to have an idea about the keywords</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Do indulge in technique of Braindump i.e. jotting down the ideas in an organized format that strikes your mind.</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use tools like Buzzsumo that tells social media engagements of your generated content.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Content Ideation Process</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">New ideas can be generated with the help of a Content Ideation Process. The steps are as follows:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">New combination of old ideas</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Gathering raw material</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Digesting material</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Unconscious processing</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Eureka Moment</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"2\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Build Content Creation Framework</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Content creation is essential to the success of your Inbound Marketing. If you want to be found in the search engines for the phrases that your potential customers search for, then you will have to build an effective content creation framework. An effective framework for content marketing will mean that it has to be repeatable, organized and agile. That’s when you have a proven structure to produce quality content.  You will need to create educational, informative, useful content for your audience based on your detailed understanding of buyer’s personas and the stage that they are at within their buyer’s journey.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>How to build a </strong><strong>Content Creation Framework ?</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Conceptualizing your content</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Planning and setting timelines</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Creating a workflow</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Reviewing your content</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Publishing on different digital platforms and promotion</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Organizing it internally</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Analyzing the results</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"3\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Business Story Telling</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">People don’t buy what you do. They buy why you do it. The aim of writing a good content should be to educate and teach your audience, thereby creating an alignment between your business and customers. There are three elements of story telling namely Character, Conflict and Resolution.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Character: </strong>Character consists of First Person: Author i.e. I, Second Person: Audience i.e. You and Third Person: He/ She which may consist of case studies about your customers.</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Conflict: </strong>A good content includes a conflict that fits your prospect’s problems, needs and buyer’s journey stage.</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Resolution: </strong>It includes an effective call to action.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"4\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Content Promotions</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Content Promotion is the distribution of content through various media channels like Facebook, Linkedin, Twitter, Instagram, Pinterest, Websites etc. Content Promotions are of two types i.e. <strong>Organic Promotions</strong> which includes SEO, Email Marketing, Social Media Promotions, Influencer, word of mouth, live events and webinars. Second type of Content Promotions are <strong>Paid Promotions </strong>that targets highly specific customers. Examples of Paid Promotions are Search Engine Ads and Social media Ads.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Content Promotion Best Practices:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Include Content optimization to enhance the outcome of your promotion plan</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Include link to landing page and appropriate call to action</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use content promotion calendar to keep a track of the consistency of the content marketing efforts</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use technique of Experimentation and Segmentation to create a list of customers based on their interests.</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Analyze results of the published content</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"5\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Repurposing Content</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Are you struggling to come up with new content? Repurposing content is a little-known secret that all smart marketers use to keep driving traffic to their site. There is no doubt that content marketing will enhance your Brand awareness but the problem is, creating content takes a lot of time and effort.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">But what if your best content could go to work for you, again and again, without your having to create anything new? That’s when Repurposing content comes into picture. It is the technique of republishing and recycling your content on different digital media.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">These are big <strong>benefits</strong> that you can’t afford to ignore. If you are <em>not </em>repurposing your content, you are missing out on a huge opportunity for your business.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Allows you to reach more potential customers</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Get more organic search engine traffic</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Improves Search Engine Optimization</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Stop stressing over what to write about</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Supports consistency and create content on ongoing basis</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Devote more time towards making sales</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Now that you know why you should be doing it, let’s look at <strong>Repurposing best Practices</strong>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use internal links and call to action in blogs</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use canonical Tags</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Wait atleast two weeks before republishing content</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Upgrade and update the content that needs to be reposted</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Modify the headline</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Pick only your top performing content and not all the content</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Repost the content on popular website that matches your business</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"6\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Analyzing and Measuring Content Marketing Efforts</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">After producing carefully thought content and distributing it to your audience, the next step is to measure the success of your efforts. Why? Because data is necessary for continual improvement. And if you don’t see results you want, you need to change the status quo. By including a measurement strategy into your content marketing initiative, you can adjust your approach, delivery and determine all possible paths to customer conversion.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Areas of focus in analyzing content:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Brand awareness</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Customer engagement</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Lead Generation</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Customer Conversion and Sales</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Customer Loyalty and retention</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Website Performance</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\" start=\"7\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Developing a Growth Marketing mentality</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Growth Marketing is an integrated approach to grow your business and optimizing your content marketing efforts through constant testing across marketing channels. Various departments which you need to focus for growth marketing are Customer service support, Sales Team, Products and Service Team.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Metrics to focus on:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Traffic on website and social media platforms</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Cost to acquire customers</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Qualified Leads</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Qualified Leads to SQL</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Conversion Rate</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Repeat Customer Rate</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Month over month growth</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Year over year growth</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">If you focus your energy on telling good business story with a carefully strategized content, no matter on which platform or in what context, will win in the long run. Yelling louder won’t help you anymore, only yelling better things will.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>So what’s your story? Are you using content marketing already?</em></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>','','','inherit','closed','closed','','279-revision-v1','','','2018-02-12 16:16:29','2018-02-12 16:16:29','',279,'http://www.richarajput.com/279-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
